    "description": "Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners is actively seeking a talented and motivated Consultant Physician to join our dynamic team in Coimbatore. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners:\nVijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in BLS/ACLS\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Flexible working hours\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Vijaya Diagnostics South Asia Partners!",
